title: Jacqueline Elledge
text:
Jacqueline Lucienne Marie-Louise Marguerite Elledge (born 8 January 1937) is an English former <a href="cricket">cricket</a>er who played primarily as a <a href="Batting%20%28cricket%29">batter</a>. She appeared in 3 <a href="Women%27s%20Test%20cricket">Test matches</a> for <a href="England%20women%27s%20cricket%20team">England</a> in 1963, in a <a href="Australian%20women%27s%20cricket%20team%20in%20England%20in%201963">series</a> against <a href="Australia%20women%27s%20national%20cricket%20team">Australia</a>. She played domestic cricket for <a href="Kent%20Women%20cricket%20team">Kent</a>.
Elledge was educated at <a href="Wolverhampton%20Girls%27%20High%20School">Wolverhampton Girls' High School</a>, where she played in the cricket team alongside <a href="Rachael%20Heyhoe%20Flint">Rachael Heyhoe Flint</a> and <a href="Ann%20Jago">Ann Jago</a>.
